07/10/2002
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg completed his first official visit to neighbouring Turkey on Sunday (6 October). 
During the four-day trip he met with his counterpart Bulent Ecevit, President Ahmet Necdet Sezer, and other officials. 
Talks focused on business contacts between the two countries, joint infrastructure and energy projects and the bid by a Turkish consortium, Koc Holding and Turk Telekom, for Bulgaria's fixed-line monopoly, BTC. 
Turkish officials also reiterated their full support for Bulgaria's membership in NATO. 
(Dnevnik, Standart - 07/09/02; BTA, Mediapool, BBC - 06/10/02)
